0711.1880;Paulo C. Freire;Paulo C. C. Freire, Bryan A. Jacoby and Matthew Bailes;PSR J1738+0333: a new gravitational laboratory;"3 pages, 2 figures. To appear in the proceedings of ""40 Years of
  Pulsars: Millisecond Pulsars, Magnetars, and More"", August 12-17, 2007,
  McGill University, Montreal, Canada";AIPConf.Proc.983:488-490,2008;10.1063/1.2900281;;astro-ph;;"  We describe in this paper a new binary millisecond pulsar, PSR J1738+0333.
Using Arecibo, we have achieved good timing accuracy for this object, about 220
ns for 1-hour integrations over 100 MHz. This allowed us to measure a precise
